Test Case Data

Example network cases in examples/cases/ are derived from public reference
datasets. No upstream source files are shipped verbatim; all cases are
converted to Surge's native format. Per-case provenance is documented in
each directory's PROVENANCE.md file.

MATPOWER (https://github.com/MATPOWER/matpower)
Copyright (C) 1996-2024 Power Systems Engineering Research Center (PSERC)
Reference: R. D. Zimmerman, C. E. Murillo-Sanchez, and R. J. Thomas,
"MATPOWER: Steady-State Operations, Planning, and Analysis Tools for Power
Systems Research and Education," IEEE Transactions on Power Systems, vol. 26,
no. 1, pp. 12-19, Feb. 2011.

The following cases originate from the MATPOWER case library and are licensed
under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC-BY-4.0):
case13659pegase, case6470rte, case6515rte, case9241pegase, case_ACTIVSg2000,
case_ACTIVSg10k.

The Polish system cases (case2383wp, case3120sp) originate from the MATPOWER
case library. Case-specific rights come from the underlying data source as
noted in each case's file header.

Texas A&M Electric Grid Test Case Repository
(https://electricgrids.engr.tamu.edu)
The following cases are sourced from the Texas A&M repository, which states
that its test cases are free for commercial or non-commercial use: case9,
case14, case30, case57, case118, case300. These cases share common lineage
